    <h2>Iridium</h2>
        <a target="_blank" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00BX7TJ2O/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=B00BX7TJ2O&linkCode=as2&tag=dinap02-20&linkId=AYCV6LGT5ENLTSZE"><img border="0" src="http://ws-na.amazon-adsystem.com/widgets/q?_encoding=UTF8&ASIN=B00BX7TJ2O&Format=_SL250_&ID=AsinImage&MarketPlace=US&ServiceVersion=20070822&WS=1&tag=dinap02-20" ></a><img src="http://ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=dinap02-20&l=as2&o=1&a=B00BX7TJ2O" width="1" height="1" border="0" alt="" style="border:none !important; margin:0px !important;" />
        <a target="_blank" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00I6EY01C/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=B00I6EY01C&linkCode=as2&tag=dinap02-20&linkId=DE3FI3DLCEZTQJL4"><img border="0" src="http://ws-na.amazon-adsystem.com/widgets/q?_encoding=UTF8&ASIN=B00I6EY01C&Format=_SL250_&ID=AsinImage&MarketPlace=US&ServiceVersion=20070822&WS=1&tag=dinap02-20" ></a><img src="http://ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=dinap02-20&l=as2&o=1&a=B00I6EY01C" width="1" height="1" border="0" alt="" style="border:none !important; margin:0px !important;" />
    <p>
        The Iridium Satellite network has 66 satellites in low earth orbit (compared to just 12 for Cospas-Sarsat).
        These satellites orbit in a complicated series of shells, providing total coverage of all points on the globe at all times.
        They also provide the ability to send and receive messages--features available on the two DeLorme inReach devices.
        Of the three networks, it has the best real-time coverage.  Are there any downsides?
    <ul>
        <li>You'll need to pay for a subscription.</li>
        <li>The network is privately owned.  If you call for help, the signal is first passed through the private control centers before reaching government search+rescue</li>
        <li>Transmission power in these devices is lower (about 2W compared to 5W) than the PLBs above.  This might mean a slightly lower chance your signal gets through in the event of tree cover, storms, etc.</li>
    </ul>
    </p>
